cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.SI

The paper presents a machine learning algorithm for crop yield prediction, which involves integrating multiple data sources and learning spatial-temporal features. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on developing a novel machine learning algorithm for crop yield prediction. The other categories are also relevant, as the paper involves data integration, feature learning, and spatial-temporal modeling, which are common topics in these sub-fields.
